  • New TFE modules being released. This will also include TFE modules, that have been refactored for a given service
  • Fixes applied to existing TFE modules
  • Enhancements (new features) applied to existing TFE modules
  • Any of existing TFE modules have been removed from the Service Catalog registry

DB Module Updates (10/13)Release Date: | Non-compliant DB Modules Removed

The below DB modules have been removed from the TFE Registry. The DB modules are being standardized by incorporating Anthem-standard parameter/option groups & other configurations. To offer the DB modules as part of Service Catalog offering, we have to also solution for packaging the post scripts which go along with the specific DB modules. These scripts are owned and authored by DBAs and need to be executed on the provisioned DB, to make it Anthem-compliant. Hence on the request of DBAs, we have removed the DB modules from the registry to prevent non-compliant DB being provisioned, as the post scripts are not integrated with the DB modules yet. We are working towards the end-state solution, where the app teams can use the DB TFE modules for provisioning & also have the post scripts executed without any developer/DBA intervention. Once we have worked through the end-state solution, we shall release the DB modules for app consumption, post DBA approvals.

In the meantime, which we have termed as MVP-1, the app teams have to work with the DBAs who shall provision the requested DB (using refactored DB TFE modules) in their AWS accounts, and also execute the post scripts manually. Please reach out to for any assistance required in provisioning databases in Anthem Cloud
